---
import BrandLayout from "../layouts/BrandLayout.astro";
---

<BrandLayout active="about" title="About | Zachary Lewis" description="Zachary Lewis went from building a 100K+ audience in video to shipping AI systems that run real businesses.">
  <!-- Header -->
  <section class="relative overflow-hidden border-b border-ink">
    <div class="absolute inset-0 bg-transparent"></div>
    <div class="relative max-w-6xl mx-auto px-4 sm:px-6 py-20 md:py-28 grid md:grid-cols-5 gap-10 items-center">
      <div class="md:col-span-3">
        <span class="text-xs font-semibold uppercase tracking-wider text-accent">About</span>
        <h1 class="mt-3 text-4xl md:text-5xl font-black text-ink leading-tight">
          From 25M views to AI that runs the business.
        </h1>
        <p class="mt-5 text-lg text-ink/80 leading-relaxed">
          I'm Zachary Lewis — a builder from Detroit. I spent years learning how to capture attention,
          then turned that obsession toward AI systems that capture <em>work</em>.
        </p>
      </div>
      <div class="md:col-span-2">
        <div class="aspect-square w-full max-w-sm rounded-2xl overflow-hidden border border-ink bg-paper2">
          <img src="/profile-photo.jpg" alt="Zachary Lewis" class="w-full h-full object-cover" loading="lazy" />
        </div>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>

  <!-- Story -->
  <section class="max-w-3xl mx-auto px-4 sm:px-6 py-16 md:py-24">
    <div class="prose prose-invert max-w-none text-ink/80 text-lg leading-relaxed space-y-5">
      <p>
        Hi, I'm Zach. I build and design AI systems that change the way you work — and I came at it from an
        unusual direction.
      </p>
      <p>
        For years I wasn't an engineer. I was a storyteller. I built a video production business and grew an
        audience of <strong>100K+ followers and 25M+ views</strong> — learning the thing most technical people
        never do: how to make people actually <em>care</em>, how attention really moves, and how to ship something
        every single day.
      </p>
      <p>
        Then in 2024, AI clicked for me, and I haven't stopped building since. Voice agents, mobile apps, real-time
        platforms — and eventually <strong>AgentlandOS</strong>, an operating system of AI agents that now runs the
        day-to-day across my own companies: fielding customer inquiries, booking jobs, chasing down leads, and
        reporting the numbers back to me every morning. Along the way I shipped <strong>TraceTrack</strong> (the
        GitHub for AI workflows), an agent-based trading system, and a shelf of free tools I give away because
        they're useful.
      </p>
      <p>
        Here's what all of it taught me: most people <em>talk</em> about AI. Very few make it actually do the work.
        The gap isn't the models — it's building systems that show up, run, and don't need babysitting.
      </p>
      <p>
        That's where I come in. If you're a founder or a creative team buried in repetitive, manual work — the
        inbox, the follow-ups, the busywork that quietly eats your week — I design and build the systems that take
        it off your plate. The result: <strong>10+ hours back a week</strong> and software that keeps running while
        you sleep. No slide decks, no demos that fall apart — working systems you can click, run, and watch do the job.
      </p>
      <p>
        I move fast, I build in the open, and I care more about what <em>runs</em> than what impresses in a meeting.
        I've always believed the fastest way to understand something is to build it — and that the best tools quietly
        give people their time back.
      </p>
      <p>
        If that's the kind of partner you're looking for, <a href="/contact" class="text-accent font-semibold">let's build something</a>.
        And if you just want to see how I think, <a href="/tools" class="text-accent font-semibold">the free tools are yours</a> — no signup.
      </p>
    </div>
  </section>

  <!-- CTA -->
  <section class="border-t border-ink bg-paper2">
    <div class="max-w-3xl mx-auto px-4 sm:px-6 py-16 text-center">
      <h2 class="text-2xl md:text-3xl font-bold text-ink mb-4">Let's build something that runs itself.</h2>
      <a href="/contact" class="inline-block px-7 py-3.5 rounded-xl bg-accent text-white border border-ink font-semibold hover:opacity-90 transition-opacity">
        Get in touch
      </a>
    </div>
  </section>
</BrandLayout>
